{
  "texts": [
    "arXiv was included as a preprint repository, which is widely used in the fields of physics, computer science, and related areas.",
    "SSRN was chosen for its emphasis on social sciences and interdisciplinary research, and its frequent use for impactful blockchain-related publications.",
    "Other databases, such as ScienceDirect, Scopus, and JSTOR were not included because of their overlapping coverage with the selected databases and access limitations.",
    "Furthermore, to identify relevant secondary literature, three search engines (Google.com, Bing.com, and Yahoo.com) were used.",
    "Key words such as 'Decentralized Science', 'DeSci,' 'blockchain technology,' 'values,' 'principles,' 'decentralized autonomous organizations,' and 'DAO' were used to identify relevant publications."
  ]
}